The paper proposes a Bayesian version of Neural Ordinary Differential Equations (N-ODEs) that enables well-calibrated quantification of prediction uncertainty. The paper combines Bayesian Neural Nets (BNNs) with Stochastic Differential Equations (SDEs) to model the flow of the activation map in time. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
